    <data key="d0">Jubilant FoodWorks: Driving a Quality Customer Experience Using Data Lake</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G07keU4g-LU</data>
    <data key="d2">Jubilant Foodworks (Domino's, Dunkin' Donuts franchisee) handles ~200,000 pizzas daily with ~1,000-1,500 orders/minute peak. The architecture addresses challenges of scale and data availability, moving from multiple 'versions of truth' and high data latency (weeks for campaign insights) to a unified data lake and warehouse solution on AWS. Key design decisions include using S3 as a data lake, EMR for ETL, Redshift for hot data, and Redshift Spectrum/Athena for cost-effective querying of cold/warm data in S3. Future plans include integrating more data sources (HRIS, SAP) and leveraging SageMaker for ML-driven forecasting and personalization.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive, other</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
